{
  "texts": [
    "All the hyperparameter settings for MIDAS training are listed in Supplementary Table 14.",
    "Implementation of comparing methodsWe compared MIDAS with 19 recent methods on different trimodal and bimodal integration tasks (see Supplementary Table 3 for an overview).",
    "If a method cannot handle missing features for a certain modality, we used the feature intersection of different batches of that modality for integration.",
    "For a fair comparison, we set the size of the low-dimensional representations generated by each method to be 32, the same as that of the biological states inferred by MIDAS.",
    "For other settings of each method, if not specified, their default values were used."
  ]
}